│    </execute_bash>                                           │
│                                                              │
│ 5. **Conclusion**: By correcting                             │
│ `ScalarEvolution::getMulExpr` to respect the `nsw` flag when │
│ multiplying by a constant, we prevent the creation of an     │
│ incorrect symbolic expression. When potential                │
│ `nsw`-violating overflow is detected for `X * C`, SCEV will  │
│ return a `SCEVUnknown`. This will cause                      │
│ `constraint-elimination` to be more conservative and avoid   │
│ the miscompilation, as it will no longer be able to "prove"  │
│ that `%cmp2` is always true. This fixes the bug at its       │
│ source in the analysis that feeds the transformation pass.   │
